---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Getting Started">
  <div class="prose">
    <h1>Getting started</h1>
    <p>This guide walks you through installing the design system in a new or existing React project.</p>

    <h2>Requirements</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Node.js ≥ 18</li>
      <li>React ≥ 18</li>
      <li>A bundler that supports CSS imports (Vite, Next.js, webpack 5+)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>1. Install packages</h2>
    <pre><code>pnpm add @ds/tokens @ds/components</code></pre>

    <h2>2. Import tokens CSS</h2>
    <p>
      Add the token CSS import to your app's entry point. This registers all CSS variables globally.
    </p>
    <pre><code>{`// main.tsx or _app.tsx
import '@ds/tokens/css';`}</code></pre>

    <h2>3. Import component styles</h2>
    <pre><code>{`import '@ds/components/styles';`}</code></pre>

    <h2>4. Use components</h2>
    <pre><code>{`import { Button } from '@ds/components';

export function App() {
  return <Button variant="primary">Hello</Button>;
}`}</code></pre>

    <h2>Dark mode</h2>
    <p>
      Add the <code>dark</code> class to your root element (or use the <code>data-theme="dark"</code> attribute).
      All semantic tokens automatically switch to their dark-mode values.
    </p>
    <pre><code>{`// Toggle dark mode
document.documentElement.classList.toggle('dark');`}</code></pre>

    <h2>TypeScript</h2>
    <p>All components and tokens are fully typed. No additional <code>@types</code> packages are required.</p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
